      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "Concept ACK. Note though that neither of these packages is a build-time dependency, unlike any of the other packages that are mentioned in `build-unix.md`. It is necessary to *run* Qt5 software with a wayland backend, but the build itself is (as far as I know) Qt backend independent. \r\n\r\n(This is the case for builds against the system libraries because distributions ship Qt5 as a shared library, and [the package](https://packages.ubuntu.com/hirsute/amd64/qtwayland5/filelist) contains a set of shared libraries loaded at run time)",
